The purpose of the game is to clear the screen of dots
while avoiding the nasties.

However by eating one of the pulsating energy pills, the roles are reversed
for a short time and you can gain points by catching the fleeing monsters.

When the screen is cleared you proceed to the next level.

Collect goodies, that appear every now and then, to gain bonus points.













 CD-MAN  Pre-release June 89                                           The Menu
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

Move around the Menu with the cursor keys, choose item either by the
up and down keys or the first letter of your choice.

At any point any time you can always return to the Menu by pressing ESC.

If you exit from gameplay with ESC you can always continue your game by
choosing CONTINUE.















 CD-MAN  Pre-release June 89                                The Highscore Table
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

The highscore table shows the ten best scores, the players name and the time
and date the game was played.
It also holds these entries for the last player ( or players if the last game
was a two-player game ).

The highscore table is contained in the file HIGHSC.CDM.
If you want to start over with an empty highscore table you can simply
delete the file and CD-MAN will create a new one with the current
date and time and reasonably low scores.

OBS!  The highscore table will only be saved if you exit the game with the
      QUIT option in the menu!










 CD-MAN  Pre-release June 89                               The Statistics Table
컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴컴

If you press the spacebar at the highscore table you will see the
statistics table.

The entries are:

Active game time  -  The time the game was actually played, that is the time
                     spent in the menu, help screens and so on is not included.

Screen / Level    -  The number of screens reached and the level on the
                     last screen.

Average speed     -  A measure of the average speed relatively to the other
                     players.

Moves made        -  Total number of moves made, one move being the distance
                     between two dots.

Monsters / Bonus  -  Total number of monsters resp. bonuses taken.




